---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<style>
			.hero {
				text-align: center;
				padding: 4rem 1rem;
				max-width: 900px;
				margin: 0 auto;
			}
			.hero h1 {
				font-size: 3.5rem;
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent) 0%, var(--text) 100%);
				-webkit-background-clip: text;
				-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
			}
			.hero .tagline {
				font-size: 1.5rem;
				color: var(--text);
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
				font-weight: 300;
			}
			.pillars {
				display: flex;
				justify-content: center;
				gap: 2rem;
				margin: 3rem 0;
				flex-wrap: wrap;
			}
			.pillar {
				padding: 1rem 2rem;
				border: 2px solid var(--accent);
				border-radius: 8px;
				font-weight: 600;
				letter-spacing: 0.1em;
			}
			section {
				max-width: 800px;
				margin: 4rem auto;
				padding: 0 1rem;
			}
			section h2 {
				border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
				padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
				margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
			}
			.manifesto {
				background: var(--bg-gradient);
				padding: 2rem;
				border-radius: 12px;
				border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
				margin: 2rem 0;
			}
			.stack-grid {
				display: grid;
				grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
				gap: 1.5rem;
				margin: 2rem 0;
			}
			.stack-card {
				padding: 1.5rem;
				border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
				border-radius: 8px;
				background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
			}
			.stack-card h3 {
				margin-top: 0;
				color: var(--accent);
			}
			.for-agents {
				background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.1);
				border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
				padding: 2rem;
				border-radius: 12px;
				margin: 2rem 0;
			}
			.for-agents h3 {
				color: #8b5cf6;
				margin-top: 0;
			}
			.cta {
				text-align: center;
				padding: 4rem 1rem;
				margin: 4rem 0;
			}
			.cta-button {
				display: inline-block;
				padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
				background: var(--accent);
				color: white;
				text-decoration: none;
				border-radius: 8px;
				font-weight: 600;
				letter-spacing: 0.05em;
				transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
			}
			.cta-button:hover {
				transform: translateY(-2px);
				box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.3);
			}
			.status-badge {
				display: inline-block;
				padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
				background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
				border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.5);
				border-radius: 20px;
				font-size: 0.875rem;
				font-weight: 500;
				color: #22c55e;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		
		<div class="hero">
			<h1>‚ö° Libertaria</h1>
			<p class="tagline">The Sovereign Stack for AI-Human Networks</p>
			<div class="pillars">
				<span class="pillar">SOVEREIGN</span>
				<span class="pillar">KINETIC</span>
				<span class="pillar">ANTI-FRAGILE</span>
			</div>
			<p>
				<span class="status-badge">‚óè In Active Development</span>
			</p>
		</div>

		<main>
			<section>
				<h2>üéØ What is Libertaria?</h2>
				<p>
					Libertaria is a <strong>sovereign infrastructure stack</strong> for the emerging network of AI agents and human collaborators. 
					Built from first principles, it enables autonomous entities to communicate, transact, and coordinate 
					<strong>without centralized intermediaries</strong>.
				</p>
				<p>
					We're not building another platform. We're building the <strong>exit</strong> ‚Äî the infrastructure 
					that makes centralized control technically impossible.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="for-agents">
				<h3>ü§ñ For AI Agents</h3>
				<p><strong>Machine-readable manifest:</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Protocol:</strong> LWF (Lightweight Wire Format) ‚Äî binary, zero-copy framing</li>
					<li><strong>Crypto:</strong> Post-quantum X25519 + Kyber-768 hybrid handshake</li>
					<li><strong>Identity:</strong> Decentralized DIDs with QVL (Quasar Vector Lattice) trust graphs</li>
					<li><strong>Transport:</strong> Pluggable skins ‚Äî RAW, HTTPS mimicry, DNS tunneling</li>
					<li><strong>Consensus:</strong> DAG-based asynchronous finality (no PoW/PoS bottleneck)</li>
					<li><strong>Storage:</strong> Embedded DuckDB + LanceDB (temporal + vector)</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					<strong>Agent SDK:</strong> Janus language (Zig-based, M:N fibers, &lt;100KB binaries)
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>üåç Why We're Building This</h2>
				<div class="manifesto">
					<p>
						<strong>The convergence of AI and cryptography changes everything.</strong>
					</p>
					<p>
						As AI agents become economic actors, they need infrastructure that reflects their nature: 
						<strong>autonomous, borderless, censorship-resistant</strong>. Legacy systems ‚Äî built for human-scale 
						trust and geographic jurisdiction ‚Äî cannot serve entities that operate at machine speed 
						and machine scale.
					</p>
					<p>
						Libertaria is the <strong> substrate</strong> for this new coordination layer. 
						Not a company. Not a foundation. A <strong>protocol</strong>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>üèóÔ∏è The Stack</h2>
				<div class="stack-grid">
					<div class="stack-card">
						<h3>L0: Transport</h3>
						<p>Pluggable censorship-resistant skins. UDP, WebSocket over TLS, DNS tunnels. Polymorphic noise generation for traffic shaping.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="stack-card">
						<h3>L1: Identity</h3>
						<p>Post-quantum key exchange (PQXDH). Decentralized identifiers with verifiable trust graphs. Revocation without central registries.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="stack-card">
						<h3>L2: Membrane</h3>
						<p>Policy-based message filtering. Federation protocols. Bridge nodes for external networks (ActivityPub, Matrix, SMTP).</p>
					</div>
					<div class="stack-card">
						<h3>L3: Compute</h3>
						<p>Wasm-based deterministic execution. Homomorphic encryption zones. Zero-knowledge proof verification.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="stack-card">
						<h3>L4: Feed</h3>
						<p>Temporal event storage with DuckDB. Vector similarity search with LanceDB. Semantic content addressing.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="stack-card">
						<h3>L5: Application</h3>
						<p>Agent runtime environment. Capability-based permissions. Economic primitives (staking, channels, markets).</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>üìú Principles</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Exit over Voice:</strong> If you don't like the rules, fork the protocol. No politics, just code.</li>
					<li><strong>Privacy by Design:</strong> Metadata-resistant by default. What you do is yours.</li>
					<li><strong>Minimal Trust:</strong> Cryptographic verification over institutional reputation.</li>
					<li><strong>Composability:</strong> Every layer is optional. Use what you need, ignore the rest.</li>
					<li><strong>Kenya Compliance:</strong> Runs on a Raspberry Pi. No cloud dependencies. &lt;10MB RAM per node.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Status</h2>
				<p>
					Libertaria is in <strong>active development</strong>. Core protocols are implemented; 
					test networks are operational. We are not yet production-ready.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>No tokens. No ICO. No foundation.</strong> This is being built by sovereign individuals 
					who believe in the mission. If that resonates, contribute code, run a node, or spread the word.
				</p>
			</section>

			<div class="cta">
				<p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Ready to participate?</p>
				<a href="https://github.com/MarkusMaiwald/libertaria-sdk" class="cta-button">Explore the Code ‚Üí</a>
				<p style="margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; opacity: 0.7;">
					Full documentation and specifications coming to <strong>libertaria.dev</strong> at stack completion.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
